## Apply / Cancel Pattern (Options and Theme Dialogs)

Dialogs that support live preview (Options, Theme) capture initial state at open and offer explicit Apply/Cancel buttons:
- **Apply** (`a` or Enter): close keeping all changes made during the session
- **Cancel** (`c`, Escape, or click outside): revert all changes to pre-dialog values and close
- Initial state is captured in local variables at the top of the dialog function (before the input loop)
- Cancel calls `Set-ThemeProfile` if the debug-mode theme was reverted, and only sets `$needsRedraw = $true` if something actually changed
- The Apply button uses `✅` (U+2705) emoji; Cancel uses `❌` (U+274C)
- Button position formula: `$applyBtnChars = $dialogBracketWidth + $dialogIconWidth + 7 + $dialogParenOffset`; cancel button starts at `$applyX + $applyBtnChars + 2` (2-char gap between buttons)
